;self-fulfilling prophecy&quot; is a process whereby a belief or expectation, correct or incorrect, affects the outcome of a situation or the way a person or group will behave.<br><br>Elliot Aronson<br>Best known for the invention of the Jigsaw Classroom as a method of reducing interethnic hostility and prejudice.","filename":"1481479867912","ext":".png","w":638,"h":640,"tn_w":249,"tn_h":250,"tim":1492613786839,"time":1492613786,"md5":"AFxoeIcl\/8gyDniWd1mQmA==","fsize":212277,"resto":0,"id":"z5vid\/FT","country":"PT","bumplimit":0,"imagelimit":0,"semantic_url":"fathers-of-social-psychology","country_name":"Portugal","replies":0,"images":0,"unique_ips":1}]}